{
  "texts": [
    "Policymakers looking to use data-driven methods for their decision making can use the RST method to gain insight across the many tiers and dynamics present in a supply chain.",
    "For the more obvious dynamics, such as those seen for Canada in the copper wire tier in this case study, RST provides reinforcement to the importance of exposure to risk in a supply chain.",
    "On the other hand, the less obvious results may challenge how policymakers and managers have been taught to think about supply risk.",
    "The instinct is to focus only on the big players: the dominant producer, the key logistics hub, the one supplier that everyone depends on.",
    "Protecting these nodes seems like common sense."
  ]
}